The Dataset

Who collected the data? - Bureau of Justice Statistics (BJS) data collections funded by Robert W. Wilson Charitable Trust

How was the data collected or generated?
- The prison variables draw on the National Correction Reporting Program (NCRP) (collect individual data on admissions and releases since 1983) and directly from state departments of correction is NCRP data is not available or is unreliable. - The jails data draws on the Annual Survey of Jails (ASJ)(samples of counties since 1982), Census of Jails (COJ)(data on all counties since its first collection in 1970), and population and admissions variables from Death in Custody Reporting Program (DCRP) (facility-level jail population and admissions data 2000-2013). The ASJ and COJ are combines to create jail variables. -Separate variables are created using DCRP data. - Dataset also includes the population estimates collected by the US Census Bureau and the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), geographic information from USDA. 32

Why was the data collected?
- To provide detail on the sources and variables in the Incarceration Trends over time for the entire US. This involves county-level data on prison and jail incarceration and related measures as well.
